{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016rV4RbuJJmMJCSvE2Ax7n3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The highest priority user story with `passes: false` is US-007 (priority 7): \"Submit connections to Supabase\". Let me look at what's needed:\n\n1. A \"Submit\" / \"Send\" button visible once at least one connection is drawn\n2. Pressing submit sends connections to Supabase via JS SDK\n3. Each connection as its own row with session_id, source_box, target_box\n4. session_id is a unique anonymous ID from crypto.randomUUID() stored in localStorage\n5. Submit button disabled/hidden after successful submission\n6. Error handling with retry\n7. Supabase table allows anonymous inserts\n\n\n8. Once submitted, can't modify/resubmit — localStorage tracks submitted state\n\nI notice US-009 (Set up Supabase table) is a dependency with priority 9, but since US-007 is the highest priority failing story, I should tackle that first. Setting up the Supabase table will likely be part of implementing US-007 anyway.\n\nLet me start by examining the existing codebase to understand the current structure and see if there's already a table in place.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6533,"cache_read_input_tokens":24343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6533},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dcac71c0-5063-4a7e-9a0d-0e0cd9cdbd6d","uuid":"29060fd0-34ff-4525-b748-605fe98c3dd2"}
