{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RYywiEE3CJL6keMx9RhPvH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"US-010 is complete. There are still stories with `passes: false` (US-011 and US-012), so another iteration will pick those up.\n\n**Summary of US-010 implementation:**\n- Created a Supabase RPC function `get_aggregate_connections()` for server-side aggregation (GROUP BY with COUNT)\n- Exported `drawConnection` from `connections.ts` with a configurable `width` parameter\n- Created `src/results.ts` with `createResultsRenderer()` that manages two PIXI layers:\n  - **Aggregate layer**: draws all connections from the crowd with thickness proportional to count (1.5–10px), muted blue-grey color at 0.7 alpha\n  - **User layer**: highlights the user's own connections in red on top so they stand out\n- Wired up the \"Se resultater\" button in `main.ts` — fetches results on click, changes to \"Opdater resultater\" for refresh, shows loading/error states\n- Typecheck and build both pass"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":290,"cache_read_input_tokens":59646,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":290},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e877d12-cc08-4522-9c52-641e0b04ab62","uuid":"e9277800-3058-4203-b55b-e045771e631f"}
