{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BTMFjjLSZdnC5sxrTACPM6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- Project uses Vite + vanilla TypeScript (no framework)\n     3→- PIXI.js v8 for canvas rendering — use `new Application()` then `await app.init(...)` pattern\n     4→- Source code lives in `src/`\n     5→- npm is the package manager (no bun/pnpm)\n     6→- TypeScript strict mode enabled with `noUnusedLocals` and `noUnusedParameters`\n     7→- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` for typecheck, `npx vite build` for build\n     8→- Canvas is full-viewport with `resizeTo: window`, background `#1a1a2e`\n     9→- Box labels live in `src/config.ts` as a `BOX_LABELS` string array (0-based index, box 1 = index 0)\n    10→- Grid rendering lives in `src/grid.ts`, exports `createGrid(app)` → returns `BoxInfo[]`\n    11→- `BoxInfo` has `index`, `container`, `cx`, `cy`, `w`, `h` — needed for line drawing in future stories\n    12→- Connection logic lives in `src/connections.ts`, exports `setupConnections(app, boxes)` → returns `ConnectionManager`\n    13→- `ConnectionManager` has `connections: Connection[]` (mutable array) and `redraw()` to re-render all lines\n    14→- `Connection` interface: `{ source: number; target: number }` (0-based box indices)\n    15→- Lines use quadratic bezier curves with perpendicular offset, arrowheads at target box edge\n    16→- `touch-action: none` on canvas element prevents browser gestures from interfering with drag\n    17→- Tap vs drag detection: compare pointer movement distance against `TAP_THRESHOLD` (10px) in `endDrag`\n    18→- `selectedBoxIndex` state in `setupConnections` tracks tap-tap selection; `highlightLayer` renders the visual highlight\n    19→- Supabase client lives in `src/supabase.ts` — exports `supabase` singleton\n    20→- Submit logic lives in `src/submit.ts` — exports `isSubmitted()` and `submitConnections(connections)`\n    21→- Box indices are 0-based internally but stored as 1-based in Supabase (source_box + 1, target_box + 1)\n    22→- Session ID generated via `crypto.randomUUID()` and stored in `localStorage` key `linjer_session_id`\n    23→- Submission state tracked via `localStorage` key `linjer_submitted` (\"true\" when submitted)\n    24→- Connections saved to `localStorage` key `linjer_connections` as JSON after submission\n    25→- `getStoredConnections()` in `submit.ts` retrieves saved connections from localStorage (returns `Connection[]` 0-based)\n    26→- Results button (`#results-btn`) shares position with submit button — they're mutually exclusive in visibility\n    27→- Supabase RPC functions: `supabase.rpc('fn_name')` returns `{ data, error }` — use `SECURITY DEFINER` for anonymous access\n    28→- `drawConnection(g, source, target, color, width)` is exported from connections.ts — reusable for any line rendering\n    29→- Results rendering lives in `src/results.ts` — `createResultsRenderer(app, boxes)` returns `{ showResults, hide, visible }`\n    30→\n    31→---\n    32→\n    33→## 2026-03-02 - US-001\n    34→- Set up Vite + TypeScript project scaffold\n    35→- Installed PIXI.js v8 and created full-viewport responsive canvas\n    36→- Canvas uses `resizeTo: window`, `autoDensity: true`, and `devicePixelRatio` for crisp mobile rendering\n    37→- Added `index.html` with viewport meta (no scaling), CSS reset for full-screen canvas\n    38→- Files changed: `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, `.gitignore`\n    39→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    40→  - Vite `create` won't scaffold into a non-empty directory — set up manually instead\n    41→  - PIXI.js v8 uses async init pattern: `const app = new Application(); await app.init({...})`\n    42→  - `autoDensity: true` + `resolution: devicePixelRatio` ensures sharp rendering on high-DPI phone screens\n    43→  - The viewport meta tag needs `maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no` to prevent pinch-zoom on mobile\n    44→---\n    45→\n    46→## 2026-03-02 - US-002\n    47→- Rendered 11 boxes in a 3-3-3-2 grid layout (Tier 4 at top, Tier 1 at bottom)\n    48→- Created `src/config.ts` with `BOX_LABELS` array — easy to swap labels\n    49→- Created `src/grid.ts` with `createGrid()` that positions boxes responsively\n    50→- Boxes have rounded corners, borders, centered text labels, and adapt to screen size\n    51→- Updated `src/main.ts` to import and call `createGrid(app)`\n    52→- Files changed: `src/config.ts` (new), `src/grid.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`\n    53→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    54→  - PIXI.js v8 `Graphics` API: use `bg.roundRect(...)` then `bg.fill(...)` then `bg.stroke(...)` — chained shape → fill → stroke\n    55→  - Box numbering is 0-based internally (array index) but 1-based in user-facing context — `BOX_LABELS[0]` = box 1\n    56→  - The grid ROWS constant maps visual rows (top-to-bottom) to box indices — bottom row has 2 boxes, rest have 3\n    57→  - `BoxInfo` interface is exported for future stories (line drawing will need `cx`, `cy` for connection endpoints)\n    58→  - Text `wordWrapWidth` should be box width minus padding to keep text readable\n    59→---\n    60→\n    61→## 2026-03-02 - US-003\n    62→- Implemented drag-to-connect interaction between boxes\n    63→- Created `src/connections.ts` with full pointer event handling (pointerdown on boxes, pointermove/pointerup on stage)\n    64→- Preview line (green, semi-transparent) follows finger during drag, disappears if drag ends outside a box\n    65→- Committed connections rendered as bezier curves (quadratic, with perpendicular offset) with arrowheads\n    66→- Lines start/end at box edges using ray-box intersection calculation\n    67→- Added `touch-action: none` to canvas CSS in `index.html` for reliable mobile touch handling\n    68→- Files changed: `src/connections.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n    69→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    70→  - PIXI v8 pointer events: set `eventMode = 'static'` and `hitArea` on containers for interaction\n    71→  - Use `app.stage.hitArea = app.screen` to capture stage-level pointer events\n    72→  - `pointercancel` event should be handled on mobile (browser can steal touch for gestures)\n    73→  - For bezier arrowheads: tangent at t=1 of quadratic bezier P0,CP,P2 is direction `P2 - CP`\n    74→  - Box edge intersection: compare `|dx|/halfW` vs `|dy|/halfH` to determine which edge is hit\n    75→  - `FederatedPointerEvent.global` gives coordinates in stage space (matches CSS coords with autoDensity)\n    76→---\n    77→\n    78→## 2026-03-02 - US-004\n    79→- Added tap-tap fallback for creating connections (tap one box, then tap another)\n    80→- Distinguishes taps from drags by measuring pointer movement distance (< 10px = tap)\n    81→- Selected box gets a green highlight overlay (rounded rect with fill alpha 0.15 and stroke alpha 0.8)\n    82→- Tapping the same box twice deselects it; tapping empty space also deselects\n    83→- Both drag and tap-tap work simultaneously — drag takes precedence when movement exceeds threshold\n    84→- Added `highlightLayer` Graphics between boxes and linesLayer for proper z-ordering\n    85→- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`\n    86→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    87→  - Tap vs drag: track `dragStartX`/`dragStartY` on pointerdown, compare distance on pointerup\n    88→  - `highlightLayer` is inserted before `linesLayer` in stage children order so highlights appear behind lines\n    89→  - The green highlight uses the same color as the preview line (`SELECTED_COLOR = 0x53c28b`) for visual consistency\n    90→  - `BOX_RADIUS` (10) from grid.ts must be matched by `HIGHLIGHT_RADIUS` in connections.ts for the highlight overlay to align with box corners\n    91→- `getBezierParams(source, target)` returns `{ start, end, cpX, cpY }` — reuse for any bezier curve operation (drawing, hit testing, animation)\n    92→- For fade-out animations: create temp `Graphics` layer, decrement `layer.alpha` via `app.ticker`, `destroy()` when alpha ≤ 0\n    93→- HTML overlay elements (fixed-position buttons/toasts) work well for UI controls on top of the PIXI canvas\n    94→- `ConnectionManager` returned from `setupConnections()` has `connections`, `redraw()`, and `resetAll()`\n    95→---\n    96→\n    97→## 2026-03-02 - US-005\n    98→- Implemented connection removal via three methods: toggle (same connection again), tap on line, and both drag/tap-tap paths\n    99→- Extracted `getBezierParams` helper from `drawConnection` for reuse in hit testing and removal animation\n   100→- Added `hitTestLine` that samples 20 points along each bezier curve and checks distance to tap point (threshold: 20px)\n   101→- Added `animateRemoval` that draws the removed line on a temporary Graphics layer and fades it out over ~300ms using `app.ticker`\n   102→- Added `toggle` closure inside `setupConnections` that checks for existing connection before adding/removing\n   103→- Refactored `drawConnection` to accept an optional `color` parameter for future use (e.g., heatmap/aggregate styling)\n   104→- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`\n   105→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   106→  - `getBezierParams` returns the start/end edge points and control point — reuse for any bezier-related feature (hit testing, styling, labels)\n   107→  - PIXI v8 `Ticker.add(fn)` / `Ticker.remove(fn)` works with plain function references; no special signature required\n   108→  - For fade animations: create a temporary `Graphics`, set `layer.alpha`, decrement in ticker, then `destroy()` when done\n   109→  - Line hit testing via bezier sampling: 20 samples (t += 0.05) with a 20px threshold works well for touch targets on mobile\n   110→  - Squared distance comparison `(dx**2 + dy**2 < threshold**2)` avoids unnecessary `Math.sqrt` calls in hot loops\n   111→---\n   112→\n   113→## 2026-03-02 - US-006\n   114→- Added \"Nulstil\" (Reset) button fixed at bottom-center of screen, only visible when connections exist\n   115→- Added 3-second \"Fortryd\" (Undo) toast that appears after reset — tapping it restores all removed connections\n   116→- Extended `ConnectionManager` with `resetAll()` method that clears connections array, deselects, and redraws\n   117→- Button and toast are HTML elements overlaid on the canvas (not PIXI objects) for better touch handling and styling\n   118→- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n   119→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   120→  - HTML overlay buttons work well for UI controls on top of PIXI canvas — easier to style and more accessible than PIXI-based UI\n   121→  - `resetAll()` returns the removed connections array so callers can implement undo\n   122→  - Using `requestAnimationFrame` to poll `connections.length` for button visibility is simple and avoids needing custom events\n   123→  - Fixed-position buttons with `bottom: 24px` + `left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%)` center well on mobile\n   124→  - The `#undo-toast` sits at `bottom: 80px` to stay above the reset button without overlap\n   125→---\n   126→\n   127→## 2026-03-02 - US-007 + US-009\n   128→- Created Supabase `connections` table with columns: id (uuid PK), session_id (text), source_box (smallint), target_box (smallint), created_at (timestamptz)\n   129→- RLS enabled with policies for anonymous inserts and selects\n   130→- Installed `@supabase/supabase-js` SDK\n   131→- Created `src/supabase.ts` with Supabase client singleton (project URL + anon key)\n   132→- Created `src/submit.ts` with session ID generation, submission logic, and localStorage state management\n   133→- Added \"Send\" submit button (green, fixed bottom-right) — visible when connections exist, hidden after submission\n   134→- Added error toast (\"Noget gik galt — prøv igen\") for failed submissions with 4-second auto-dismiss\n   135→- Button shows \"Sender...\" while submitting and is disabled during request\n   136→- After successful submission: button hidden, reset button hidden, connections + session_id saved to localStorage\n   137→- Updated `main.ts` to wire up submit button, manage submitted state, and hide reset/submit after submission\n   138→- Files changed: `src/supabase.ts` (new), `src/submit.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`, `index.html`, `package.json`\n   139→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   140→  - Supabase anon key is safe to embed client-side — RLS policies control access, not the key\n   141→  - `submitConnections()` converts 0-based box indices to 1-based before inserting (source + 1, target + 1)\n   142→  - The submit button sits at `right: 24px` to avoid overlapping the centered reset button\n   143→  - Error toast at `bottom: 80px; right: 24px` to position above the submit button\n   144→  - `isSubmitted()` checks localStorage on page load — used by main.ts to skip showing submit/reset buttons\n   145→---\n   146→\n   147→## 2026-03-02 - US-008\n   148→- Added `getStoredConnections()` to `submit.ts` — retrieves saved connections from localStorage with JSON parse error handling\n   149→- On page load, if `isSubmitted()` is true, connections are restored from localStorage, pushed into `manager.connections`, and `redraw()` renders them on canvas\n   150→- Added \"Se resultater\" button (`#results-btn`) in HTML — shown after submission (both fresh and restored from localStorage)\n   151→- After fresh submission, the results button is now displayed alongside hiding submit/reset buttons\n   152→- Files changed: `src/submit.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n   153→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   154→  - `getStoredConnections()` parses `linjer_connections` from localStorage — returns `Connection[]` (0-based indices, same as internal format)\n   155→  - The `#results-btn` is positioned at `bottom: 24px; right: 24px` — same position as submit button (they're never both visible)\n   156→  - Restoring state on load: push stored connections into `manager.connections` then call `manager.redraw()` — the connections array is shared by reference\n   157→  - The results button is a placeholder for US-010 (aggregate results) — its click handler will be wired up in that story\n   158→---\n   159→\n   160→## 2026-03-02 - US-010\n   161→- Created Supabase RPC function `get_aggregate_connections()` that returns grouped connection counts (source_box, target_box, count) ordered by count DESC\n   162→- Exported `drawConnection` from `connections.ts` with configurable width parameter for reuse in aggregate rendering\n   163→- Created `src/results.ts` with `createResultsRenderer(app, boxes)` — manages two PIXI Graphics layers (aggregate + user highlights)\n   164→- Aggregate lines rendered with variable thickness proportional to count (MIN_WIDTH=1.5 to MAX_WIDTH=10), color `0x8899bb` at 0.7 alpha\n   165→- User's own connections highlighted on top in distinct red (`0xe94560`) at width 3 so they stand out\n   166→- Results button changes to \"Opdater resultater\" after first fetch, allowing refresh to see new submissions\n   167→- Loading state (\"Henter...\") and error handling with toast for failed fetches\n   168→- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `src/results.ts` (new)\n   169→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   170→  - Supabase RPC functions created via `CREATE FUNCTION ... RETURNS TABLE` + `SECURITY DEFINER` work with anonymous access\n   171→  - Call RPC via `supabase.rpc('function_name')` — returns `{ data, error }` like regular queries\n   172→  - `drawConnection` now accepts `width` parameter — callers can control line thickness for aggregate vs user lines\n   173→  - PIXI `addChildAt(child, index)` inserts at specific z-order — use `boxes.length` as insert index to place layers above boxes but below interaction layers\n   174→  - Aggregate layer at `alpha=0.7` provides good visual separation from user's own highlighted connections\n   175→---\n   176→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5713111b-d6f1-430e-8ec1-2314c52440c9","uuid":"669c9a79-4d6e-48c8-a090-6357b336ef27","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/jstoone/Sites/linjer/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- Project uses Vite + vanilla TypeScript (no framework)\n- PIXI.js v8 for canvas rendering — use `new Application()` then `await app.init(...)` pattern\n- Source code lives in `src/`\n- npm is the package manager (no bun/pnpm)\n- TypeScript strict mode enabled with `noUnusedLocals` and `noUnusedParameters`\n- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` for typecheck, `npx vite build` for build\n- Canvas is full-viewport with `resizeTo: window`, background `#1a1a2e`\n- Box labels live in `src/config.ts` as a `BOX_LABELS` string array (0-based index, box 1 = index 0)\n- Grid rendering lives in `src/grid.ts`, exports `createGrid(app)` → returns `BoxInfo[]`\n- `BoxInfo` has `index`, `container`, `cx`, `cy`, `w`, `h` — needed for line drawing in future stories\n- Connection logic lives in `src/connections.ts`, exports `setupConnections(app, boxes)` → returns `ConnectionManager`\n- `ConnectionManager` has `connections: Connection[]` (mutable array) and `redraw()` to re-render all lines\n- `Connection` interface: `{ source: number; target: number }` (0-based box indices)\n- Lines use quadratic bezier curves with perpendicular offset, arrowheads at target box edge\n- `touch-action: none` on canvas element prevents browser gestures from interfering with drag\n- Tap vs drag detection: compare pointer movement distance against `TAP_THRESHOLD` (10px) in `endDrag`\n- `selectedBoxIndex` state in `setupConnections` tracks tap-tap selection; `highlightLayer` renders the visual highlight\n- Supabase client lives in `src/supabase.ts` — exports `supabase` singleton\n- Submit logic lives in `src/submit.ts` — exports `isSubmitted()` and `submitConnections(connections)`\n- Box indices are 0-based internally but stored as 1-based in Supabase (source_box + 1, target_box + 1)\n- Session ID generated via `crypto.randomUUID()` and stored in `localStorage` key `linjer_session_id`\n- Submission state tracked via `localStorage` key `linjer_submitted` (\"true\" when submitted)\n- Connections saved to `localStorage` key `linjer_connections` as JSON after submission\n- `getStoredConnections()` in `submit.ts` retrieves saved connections from localStorage (returns `Connection[]` 0-based)\n- Results button (`#results-btn`) shares position with submit button — they're mutually exclusive in visibility\n- Supabase RPC functions: `supabase.rpc('fn_name')` returns `{ data, error }` — use `SECURITY DEFINER` for anonymous access\n- `drawConnection(g, source, target, color, width)` is exported from connections.ts — reusable for any line rendering\n- Results rendering lives in `src/results.ts` — `createResultsRenderer(app, boxes)` returns `{ showResults, hide, visible }`\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-001\n- Set up Vite + TypeScript project scaffold\n- Installed PIXI.js v8 and created full-viewport responsive canvas\n- Canvas uses `resizeTo: window`, `autoDensity: true`, and `devicePixelRatio` for crisp mobile rendering\n- Added `index.html` with viewport meta (no scaling), CSS reset for full-screen canvas\n- Files changed: `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, `.gitignore`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Vite `create` won't scaffold into a non-empty directory — set up manually instead\n  - PIXI.js v8 uses async init pattern: `const app = new Application(); await app.init({...})`\n  - `autoDensity: true` + `resolution: devicePixelRatio` ensures sharp rendering on high-DPI phone screens\n  - The viewport meta tag needs `maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no` to prevent pinch-zoom on mobile\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-002\n- Rendered 11 boxes in a 3-3-3-2 grid layout (Tier 4 at top, Tier 1 at bottom)\n- Created `src/config.ts` with `BOX_LABELS` array — easy to swap labels\n- Created `src/grid.ts` with `createGrid()` that positions boxes responsively\n- Boxes have rounded corners, borders, centered text labels, and adapt to screen size\n- Updated `src/main.ts` to import and call `createGrid(app)`\n- Files changed: `src/config.ts` (new), `src/grid.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - PIXI.js v8 `Graphics` API: use `bg.roundRect(...)` then `bg.fill(...)` then `bg.stroke(...)` — chained shape → fill → stroke\n  - Box numbering is 0-based internally (array index) but 1-based in user-facing context — `BOX_LABELS[0]` = box 1\n  - The grid ROWS constant maps visual rows (top-to-bottom) to box indices — bottom row has 2 boxes, rest have 3\n  - `BoxInfo` interface is exported for future stories (line drawing will need `cx`, `cy` for connection endpoints)\n  - Text `wordWrapWidth` should be box width minus padding to keep text readable\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-003\n- Implemented drag-to-connect interaction between boxes\n- Created `src/connections.ts` with full pointer event handling (pointerdown on boxes, pointermove/pointerup on stage)\n- Preview line (green, semi-transparent) follows finger during drag, disappears if drag ends outside a box\n- Committed connections rendered as bezier curves (quadratic, with perpendicular offset) with arrowheads\n- Lines start/end at box edges using ray-box intersection calculation\n- Added `touch-action: none` to canvas CSS in `index.html` for reliable mobile touch handling\n- Files changed: `src/connections.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - PIXI v8 pointer events: set `eventMode = 'static'` and `hitArea` on containers for interaction\n  - Use `app.stage.hitArea = app.screen` to capture stage-level pointer events\n  - `pointercancel` event should be handled on mobile (browser can steal touch for gestures)\n  - For bezier arrowheads: tangent at t=1 of quadratic bezier P0,CP,P2 is direction `P2 - CP`\n  - Box edge intersection: compare `|dx|/halfW` vs `|dy|/halfH` to determine which edge is hit\n  - `FederatedPointerEvent.global` gives coordinates in stage space (matches CSS coords with autoDensity)\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-004\n- Added tap-tap fallback for creating connections (tap one box, then tap another)\n- Distinguishes taps from drags by measuring pointer movement distance (< 10px = tap)\n- Selected box gets a green highlight overlay (rounded rect with fill alpha 0.15 and stroke alpha 0.8)\n- Tapping the same box twice deselects it; tapping empty space also deselects\n- Both drag and tap-tap work simultaneously — drag takes precedence when movement exceeds threshold\n- Added `highlightLayer` Graphics between boxes and linesLayer for proper z-ordering\n- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Tap vs drag: track `dragStartX`/`dragStartY` on pointerdown, compare distance on pointerup\n  - `highlightLayer` is inserted before `linesLayer` in stage children order so highlights appear behind lines\n  - The green highlight uses the same color as the preview line (`SELECTED_COLOR = 0x53c28b`) for visual consistency\n  - `BOX_RADIUS` (10) from grid.ts must be matched by `HIGHLIGHT_RADIUS` in connections.ts for the highlight overlay to align with box corners\n- `getBezierParams(source, target)` returns `{ start, end, cpX, cpY }` — reuse for any bezier curve operation (drawing, hit testing, animation)\n- For fade-out animations: create temp `Graphics` layer, decrement `layer.alpha` via `app.ticker`, `destroy()` when alpha ≤ 0\n- HTML overlay elements (fixed-position buttons/toasts) work well for UI controls on top of the PIXI canvas\n- `ConnectionManager` returned from `setupConnections()` has `connections`, `redraw()`, and `resetAll()`\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-005\n- Implemented connection removal via three methods: toggle (same connection again), tap on line, and both drag/tap-tap paths\n- Extracted `getBezierParams` helper from `drawConnection` for reuse in hit testing and removal animation\n- Added `hitTestLine` that samples 20 points along each bezier curve and checks distance to tap point (threshold: 20px)\n- Added `animateRemoval` that draws the removed line on a temporary Graphics layer and fades it out over ~300ms using `app.ticker`\n- Added `toggle` closure inside `setupConnections` that checks for existing connection before adding/removing\n- Refactored `drawConnection` to accept an optional `color` parameter for future use (e.g., heatmap/aggregate styling)\n- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `getBezierParams` returns the start/end edge points and control point — reuse for any bezier-related feature (hit testing, styling, labels)\n  - PIXI v8 `Ticker.add(fn)` / `Ticker.remove(fn)` works with plain function references; no special signature required\n  - For fade animations: create a temporary `Graphics`, set `layer.alpha`, decrement in ticker, then `destroy()` when done\n  - Line hit testing via bezier sampling: 20 samples (t += 0.05) with a 20px threshold works well for touch targets on mobile\n  - Squared distance comparison `(dx**2 + dy**2 < threshold**2)` avoids unnecessary `Math.sqrt` calls in hot loops\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-006\n- Added \"Nulstil\" (Reset) button fixed at bottom-center of screen, only visible when connections exist\n- Added 3-second \"Fortryd\" (Undo) toast that appears after reset — tapping it restores all removed connections\n- Extended `ConnectionManager` with `resetAll()` method that clears connections array, deselects, and redraws\n- Button and toast are HTML elements overlaid on the canvas (not PIXI objects) for better touch handling and styling\n- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - HTML overlay buttons work well for UI controls on top of PIXI canvas — easier to style and more accessible than PIXI-based UI\n  - `resetAll()` returns the removed connections array so callers can implement undo\n  - Using `requestAnimationFrame` to poll `connections.length` for button visibility is simple and avoids needing custom events\n  - Fixed-position buttons with `bottom: 24px` + `left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%)` center well on mobile\n  - The `#undo-toast` sits at `bottom: 80px` to stay above the reset button without overlap\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-007 + US-009\n- Created Supabase `connections` table with columns: id (uuid PK), session_id (text), source_box (smallint), target_box (smallint), created_at (timestamptz)\n- RLS enabled with policies for anonymous inserts and selects\n- Installed `@supabase/supabase-js` SDK\n- Created `src/supabase.ts` with Supabase client singleton (project URL + anon key)\n- Created `src/submit.ts` with session ID generation, submission logic, and localStorage state management\n- Added \"Send\" submit button (green, fixed bottom-right) — visible when connections exist, hidden after submission\n- Added error toast (\"Noget gik galt — prøv igen\") for failed submissions with 4-second auto-dismiss\n- Button shows \"Sender...\" while submitting and is disabled during request\n- After successful submission: button hidden, reset button hidden, connections + session_id saved to localStorage\n- Updated `main.ts` to wire up submit button, manage submitted state, and hide reset/submit after submission\n- Files changed: `src/supabase.ts` (new), `src/submit.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`, `index.html`, `package.json`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Supabase anon key is safe to embed client-side — RLS policies control access, not the key\n  - `submitConnections()` converts 0-based box indices to 1-based before inserting (source + 1, target + 1)\n  - The submit button sits at `right: 24px` to avoid overlapping the centered reset button\n  - Error toast at `bottom: 80px; right: 24px` to position above the submit button\n  - `isSubmitted()` checks localStorage on page load — used by main.ts to skip showing submit/reset buttons\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-008\n- Added `getStoredConnections()` to `submit.ts` — retrieves saved connections from localStorage with JSON parse error handling\n- On page load, if `isSubmitted()` is true, connections are restored from localStorage, pushed into `manager.connections`, and `redraw()` renders them on canvas\n- Added \"Se resultater\" button (`#results-btn`) in HTML — shown after submission (both fresh and restored from localStorage)\n- After fresh submission, the results button is now displayed alongside hiding submit/reset buttons\n- Files changed: `src/submit.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `getStoredConnections()` parses `linjer_connections` from localStorage — returns `Connection[]` (0-based indices, same as internal format)\n  - The `#results-btn` is positioned at `bottom: 24px; right: 24px` — same position as submit button (they're never both visible)\n  - Restoring state on load: push stored connections into `manager.connections` then call `manager.redraw()` — the connections array is shared by reference\n  - The results button is a placeholder for US-010 (aggregate results) — its click handler will be wired up in that story\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-010\n- Created Supabase RPC function `get_aggregate_connections()` that returns grouped connection counts (source_box, target_box, count) ordered by count DESC\n- Exported `drawConnection` from `connections.ts` with configurable width parameter for reuse in aggregate rendering\n- Created `src/results.ts` with `createResultsRenderer(app, boxes)` — manages two PIXI Graphics layers (aggregate + user highlights)\n- Aggregate lines rendered with variable thickness proportional to count (MIN_WIDTH=1.5 to MAX_WIDTH=10), color `0x8899bb` at 0.7 alpha\n- User's own connections highlighted on top in distinct red (`0xe94560`) at width 3 so they stand out\n- Results button changes to \"Opdater resultater\" after first fetch, allowing refresh to see new submissions\n- Loading state (\"Henter...\") and error handling with toast for failed fetches\n- Files changed: `src/connections.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `src/results.ts` (new)\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Supabase RPC functions created via `CREATE FUNCTION ... RETURNS TABLE` + `SECURITY DEFINER` work with anonymous access\n  - Call RPC via `supabase.rpc('function_name')` — returns `{ data, error }` like regular queries\n  - `drawConnection` now accepts `width` parameter — callers can control line thickness for aggregate vs user lines\n  - PIXI `addChildAt(child, index)` inserts at specific z-order — use `boxes.length` as insert index to place layers above boxes but below interaction layers\n  - Aggregate layer at `alpha=0.7` provides good visual separation from user's own highlighted connections\n---\n","numLines":176,"startLine":1,"totalLines":176}}}
