{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DvtLrftJuppQad5oNsQVjq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `THEME.aggregate` (0x8899bb = 8952251) is being compared to `THEME.line` (0xe94560 = 15287648) because the `drawConnection` function's `color` parameter defaults to `THEME.line` which is a specific numeric literal type due to `as const`.\n\nThe problem is that `THEME` uses `as const`, so all the number values become literal types. The `drawConnection` function has `color = LINE_COLOR` as default, and `LINE_COLOR` is `THEME.line` which is `0xe94560` as a literal. So when we pass `AGGREGATE_COLOR` (which is `THEME.aggregate` = `0x8899bb`), it's a different literal type.\n\n\nI need to add an explicit type annotation to the `color` parameter to widen it from the specific literal type to accept any number value.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":186,"cache_read_input_tokens":56034,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":186},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5713111b-d6f1-430e-8ec1-2314c52440c9","uuid":"32e574eb-b533-46a3-8c98-6ac5909368fc"}
