{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TkqufzchANkixfDx23hLw8","type":"tool_result","content":"   170→  - Supabase RPC functions created via `CREATE FUNCTION ... RETURNS TABLE` + `SECURITY DEFINER` work with anonymous access\n   171→  - Call RPC via `supabase.rpc('function_name')` — returns `{ data, error }` like regular queries\n   172→  - `drawConnection` now accepts `width` parameter — callers can control line thickness for aggregate vs user lines\n   173→  - PIXI `addChildAt(child, index)` inserts at specific z-order — use `boxes.length` as insert index to place layers above boxes but below interaction layers\n   174→  - Aggregate layer at `alpha=0.7` provides good visual separation from user's own highlighted connections\n   175→---\n   176→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5713111b-d6f1-430e-8ec1-2314c52440c9","uuid":"f93762f9-e2ef-41d2-97a5-61d6bbf490bc","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/jstoone/Sites/linjer/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"  - Supabase RPC functions created via `CREATE FUNCTION ... RETURNS TABLE` + `SECURITY DEFINER` work with anonymous access\n  - Call RPC via `supabase.rpc('function_name')` — returns `{ data, error }` like regular queries\n  - `drawConnection` now accepts `width` parameter — callers can control line thickness for aggregate vs user lines\n  - PIXI `addChildAt(child, index)` inserts at specific z-order — use `boxes.length` as insert index to place layers above boxes but below interaction layers\n  - Aggregate layer at `alpha=0.7` provides good visual separation from user's own highlighted connections\n---\n","numLines":7,"startLine":170,"totalLines":176}}}
